This paper deals with the problem of geotagging social media content, which involves natural language processing, machine learning, and data analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), which focuses on the study of social networks and their properties, as well as the analysis of large-scale data from social media platforms. 

The paper also involves text analysis and classification, which falls under the scope of cs.CL (Computation and Language). 

Moreover, the authors use information retrieval techniques to identify relevant content, which is related to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). 

The paper also deals with data-driven approaches and modeling, which are relevant to cs.SD (Software Engineering) and cs.CY (Computers and Society). 

Overall, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SI, cs.CL, and cs.IR, followed by cs.SD and cs.CY.
